Class CommandInvocation<OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dm.jrt.core.util.DeepEqualObject
      • com.github.dm.jrt.core.invocation.InvocationFactory<Void,OUT>
        • com.github.dm.jrt.core.invocation.CommandInvocation<OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Invocation<Void,OUT>

    public abstract class CommandInvocation<OUT>
extends InvocationFactory<Void,OUT>
implements Invocation<Void,OUT>
    Abstract implementation of an invocation performing a command (that is, no input is required) eventually returning output data.

    Note that the implementing class must not retain an internal variable state.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 06/05/2015.

        Creates and return a new invocation instance.
